text:
Watch Jets vs. Patriots: Game time, live stream, TV coverage Photo: Maddie Meyer/Getty Images Email Posted: Sun Oct. 25, 2015 
The New England Patriots will return home to host the New York Jets at Gillette Stadium on Sunday. 
New England is off to a 5–0 season for the fourth time in franchise history after defeating the Indianapolis Colts , 34–27, on Sunday. Quarterback Tom Brady threw for 312 yards and three touchdowns. 
New York’s arrival in Foxborough is highly anticipated as cornerback Darrelle Revis makes his return for the first time since leaving the Patriots for the Jets in free agency. The Jets are also riding the momentum from their 34–20 win over the Washington Redskins in Week 6. Quarterback Ryan Fitzpatrick completed 19 of 26 passes for 253 yards and two touchdowns.
